review_blob:
Taste sample @ CBC 2014 in Copenhagen.
Absolutely loved this one. The nose is so intense its silly. Peanuts!

2013 vintage. Bottle from lbutikken, Copenhagen. I kept it in my cellar for a few weeks. At first I planned to keep it there a couple of years but I changed my mind. Absolutely loved it. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Had the fortune to try a bottle at lbutikken tonight. Oh boy, this one's delicious. I could just smell the aroma for hours.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle at De Klomp Linkping. Pours dark red with slight pink head. Medium sourness. Raspberries, oak and vanilla on the nose.Not that heavy on the raspberries in the taste.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle from Mikkeller Bottle Shop the day after CBC 2013. Pours golden hazy into the glass with a white light foam that dissappears quite fast.
Balanced taste that's not that funky. I can't detect the honey by taste, but it's there in the aroma. Like it a lot.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours copper to the glass withe a sligthly tanish head
Sweet resiny notes both to the nose and tongue.
Very balanced even if there are loads of hops in the beer.
Really enjoyed this one!
Pours hazy into the glass. Clear at the top coudy at the bottom of the glass.Wonderful taste. Fruity. Piney. Curls my tongue.  Best Dipa out of Sweden yet.

Purs pitch black into the glass, with no head at all.
Aroma is full of bourbon and chocolate
Full bodied. Sweet, not much alcohol.
Taste is full of chocolate and bourbon. Hints of coffee and prunes. Maybe some over riped bananas in there as well.
Pours pitch black, with minimal head. Aroma lots of liquorice, some burnt notes, sweet. Taste is very sweet, liquorice, bitter chokolates, prunes, some coffee. Lovely one!
Pours Mahogny colored to the glass. Buttery hoppy and some flowers to the nose. Medium to full bodied with great balance between the malts and the hops. Nice Apa indeed.
Pours with a cloudy unfiltered brownish color, with a thick off white head. Really nice Imperial IPA. Very nice balance between the sweetness and the hops.
Nice lager. Pours with a thick white head. Golden color. Pretty much bitterness for a lager.
Floral, caramel to the nose, pretty much sweetness. Taste is very sweet with a medium body. Very balanced beer with lots of hops but with the sweetness of the malt that balances it perfectly. Lovely.

Bottle 355 ml. Pours as black as it gets with a minimal head. Aroma contains roasted notes, chocolate, coffe and raisins. Taste is complex with chocolate, coffee and raisins with a balanced level of bitterness. Fantastic Imperial Stout.

Bottle, 650 ml. Pours with a thick coffee/hazelnut colored head. Malty, fruity, toffee and a bit perfumy to the nose. The taste toffee ,coffee some burnt flavours and loads of hops. Surprisingly fresh. Best black IPA Ive had.
beer_name: Stone 15th Anniversary Escondidian Imperial Black IPA

review_blob: Dried apricots, citrus notes and amarillo hops to the nose. Taste is citrusy, apricots and some pine. Medium body. Fantastic DIPA. Love it.
Pours with a thick rich hazelnut colored head. Lots of anise to the nose. The taste has loads of liqourice and anise. Also picking up coffee and a bit of bitter dark chocolate. Nice one.
beer_name: Stone Imperial Russian Stout - Belgo Anise

review_blob: Sweet burned chocolate to the nose. Nice mouth fill. Burned chocolate taste aswell. Very nice IS, although not as good as the original Yeti.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Belgian Style

review_blob: Cloudy dark red beer. Nice sourness. Tastes mostly cherries. Good beer, but lambics are not a speciality of mine.
Fantastic DIPA, One of the best Ive had. Nice color, Fruity both to the nose and the mouth. Perfect body. Intense bitterness.

Sourish aroma, picking up some "amarillo" and bitter orange zest.
Taste of bananas, orange, belgic yeasts. Sweet.
